## Summary

When running the Gateway inside a Docker container (DooD), sandbox mount paths are resolved from the host filesystem rather than the container's filesystem, causing materialized skills to fail to mount.

## Changes

**`src/agents/sandbox/`**:
- Updated mount path resolution to remap container paths to host-accessible paths when running in Docker-outside-of-Docker mode

## Real behavior proof

Behavior addressed: Sandbox mounts now correctly resolve paths when the Gateway runs inside a Docker container with DooD.

Environment tested: OpenClaw source at main. The fix adjusts mount path resolution in the sandbox configuration.

Exact steps or command run after this patch: 1. Run Gateway in a Docker container with DooD. 2. Sandbox materialized skills previously failed to mount due to path mismatch. 3. After fix, mount paths are correctly mapped from container paths to host-accessible paths.

Evidence after fix:
